# 4. Building Prefix Sum

## Formula

```java
prefix[0] = arr[0];

prefix[i] = prefix[i-1] + arr[i];
```

---

## Java Code

```java
int[] prefix = new int[n];

prefix[0] = arr[0];

for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
    prefix[i] = prefix[i-1] + arr[i];
}
```

---

## Example

```text
Array

2 4 1 6 3
```

Build:

```text
2

2+4 = 6

6+1 = 7

7+6 = 13

13+3 = 16
```

Result:

```text
2 6 7 13 16
```

---

# 5. Range Sum Query

Find sum from L to R.

---

## Formula

### Case 1

```text
L == 0
```

```java
sum = prefix[R];
```

---

### Case 2

```text
L > 0
```

```java
sum = prefix[R] - prefix[L-1];
```

---

## Example

```text
Array

2 4 1 6 3

Prefix

2 6 7 13 16
```

Find:

```text
L = 1
R = 3
```

Answer:

```java
13 - 2 = 11
```

Check:

```text
4+1+6=11
```

Correct.

---

# 6. Better Prefix Sum (Interview Version)

Most interviewers prefer:

```java
int[] prefix = new int[n+1];

prefix[0] = 0;

for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
    prefix[i+1] = prefix[i] + arr[i];
}
```

---

Example

```text
Array

2 4 1 6 3
```

Prefix

```text
0 2 6 7 13 16
```

---

Range Sum:

```java
sum = prefix[R+1] - prefix[L];
```

No edge cases.

